HTML Demo


&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html&gt;
&lt;title&gt;My first website&lt;/title&gt;

&lt;body&gt;
    &lt;h1&gt; The Gettysburg Address &lt;/h1&gt;
    &lt;img src="gettysburg-address.jpg" width="200" /&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;
        &lt;a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abraham_Lincoln"&gt; Abe Lincoln &lt;/a&gt; said:
        Four score and seven years ago...
    &lt;/p&gt;

    &lt;h2&gt;What did our fathers do? &lt;/h2&gt;
    &lt;ol&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;brought forth on this continent a new nation&lt;/li&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;conceived in liberty&lt;/li&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;and dedicated to the proposition that all men are created equal&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;

&lt;/html&gt;






Recommended to show a simple demo of creating a website in Notepad++ to demystify HTML a little bit.

Open Notepad++ application on computer
Type the HTML
Save file as “GettysburgWebsite.html” à this converts it to an .html file instead of a .txt file
Close file
Locate document in File Manager, see how it is an HTML file type, and click on file. It will open in a browser and look like a website.

Cascading Style Sheets



Language to define looks of a webpage
Maintain consistency in format and style
Changes colors, sizes, spacing, fonts, etc.

h1 {
  color: red;
}

p .special {
  background-color: black;
  padding: 5px;
}




(slide 19) A web page without any styling will have a white background, black text, and standard-sized text. Cascading Style Sheets (CSS) is a language that can be used to style a web page via changes in colors, sizes, spacing, fonts, and more. This helps to maintain consistency in format and style throughout the webpage and website. To continue the bird analogy, adding CSS to your website is like the baby bird gaining colorful feathers.
Cascading Style Sheets are used to maintain consistency in format and style throughout the webpage and website.

JavaScript




Computer language that makes webpages interactive
Is it a programming language?

Yes, it is the most popular language in the world!

Runs everywhere!


&lt;html&gt;
    &lt;head&gt;
        &lt;script&gt;
function ChangeTextColor(newColor) {
   var x = document.getElementById("ColorableText");
   x.style.color = newColor;
}
        &lt;/script&gt;
    &lt;/head&gt;
    &lt;body&gt;
        &lt;p id="ColorableText"&gt;
        Click a button to change this text's color.
        &lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;button type="button" onclick="ChangeTextColor('red')"&gt;Red&lt;/button&gt;
        &lt;button type="button" onclick="ChangeTextColor('blue')"&gt;Blue&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;




(slides 20) JavaScript is a computer programming language that makes webpages interactive. This means that it provides webpages with active content, such as graphical effects, validating information in forms, and controlling pop-up windows. Remember that JavaScript code is a program, like Python is, and like other programs, it can potentially be used for nefarious purposes too (like viruses, worms, etc.). We will discuss more about Because JS introduces more functionality to a webpage, it is analogous to the bird with colorful wings now taking flight.
Programming language that provides webpages with active content: provide graphical effects, validate information in forms, pop up both useful and irritating windows, and so on (UDW pg.169)
Remember that JavaScript is a program and, like any other program, it can be used for nefarious purposes (viruses, worms, etc.)
Fun fact: at the time this was written, JavaScript was the most popular language in the world. This is because it is practically required to write a webpage. It can also be used to write a program like you would in Python.
